HEADWORD: Psoas
<hw>Pso"as</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a muscle of
the loin: cf. f. <ets>psoas</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>An
internal muscle arising from the lumbar vertebr⟦ae⟧ and inserted into
the femur. In man there are usually two on each side, and the larger
one, or great psoas, forms a part of the iliopsoas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

